 MBOMBELA –  According to a consulate official, the bodies of two men and one woman were  transported from Johannesburg and were on their way to Maputo province and Gaza. “When they got there they found out the paperwork was not in order and just dumped the coffins on the road and left.”  The relatives accompanying the bodies were put up overnight in a house in Ressano Garcia. “We contacted the government run morgue in Tonga and the bodies were kept there. Our offices in Pretoria together with the department of health arranged the paperwork.” ALSO READ: BREAKING NEWS: Grade 7 pupil allegedly assaulted in class at Valencia Combined School “The last paperwork was finished on Tuesday , all the bodies have been repatriated to Mozambique,”he concluded.